<subSubSection id="C375A0EEFFE137588EAEF8CCFEECF878" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BD0F365FFE137588EAEF8CCFEECF878" blockId="9.[151,1436,1478,2009]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis id="B91B2F77FFE137588EAEF8CCFEBAF833" bold="true" box="[199,352,1913,1938]" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">Distribution.</emphasis>
Reported from a limited part of the east coast of the Gulf of California just south of the Tropic of Cancer, from Mazatlán to Tepic, a distance of approximately 
<quantity id="4C975E80FFE137588D2EF828FC7AF814" box="[839,928,1949,1973]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" unit="km" value="200.0">200 km</quantity>
. This is north of the range of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F88E6FFE137588A82F82BFA5BF817" box="[1259,1409,1950,1974]" class="Insecta" family="Aphrophoridae" genus="Cephisus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="50" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="variolosus">
<emphasis id="B91B2F77FFE137588A82F82BFA5BF817" box="[1259,1409,1950,1974]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="50">C. variolosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at low elevation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C375A0EEFFE2375B8EAEFF2DFE3EFF56" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD0F365FFE2375B8EAEFF2DFE3EFF56" blockId="10.[151,1436,151,284]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="B91B2F77FFE2375B8EAEFF2DFEE1FF11" bold="true" box="[199,315,152,176]" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Remarks.</emphasis>
The width of the head and shortness of pronotal margins ally this species to 
<taxonomicName id="4C6F88E6FFE2375B8ACCFF2DFA93FF11" box="[1189,1353,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Aphrophoridae" genus="Cephisus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipennis">
<emphasis id="B91B2F77FFE2375B8ACCFF2DFA93FF11" box="[1189,1353,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">C. brevipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which occurs on the lowlands of the opposite side of 
<collectingCountry id="F378B3F5FFE2375B8CF3FF09FD28FF75" box="[666,754,188,212]" name="Mexico" pageId="10" pageNumber="51">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, and from which it is distinguished by the slender form, body markings and length of theca.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
